      <component>
        <section>
          <templateId root="2.16.840.1.113883.4.823.1.3.4" extension="2022-03-25" />
          <code code="81336-0" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC"
            displayName="Patient Goals, preferences, and priorities under certain health conditions" />
          <title mediaType="text/plain" representation="TXT" language="en-US">Healthcare Goals and Treatment Preferences</title>
          <text>
            <content styleCode="Bold">My Advance Care Goals</content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_1">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_priorities_criteria">If I am so sick or seriously injured that I
            cannot express my own medical treatment preferences, and if I am not expected to live
            without additional treatment for my illness, disease, condition or injury, </content>
            </content>
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_1_Q">then I want my medical care team to know that these are the things
            that are most important to me:</content>
            <list listType="ordered" ID="GPP_eol_priorities"
              styleCode="Answer">
              <item ID="GPP_eol_priorities_1-1"> Avoiding prolonged dependence on machines </item>
              <item ID="GPP_eol_priorities_1-2"> Not being a physical burden to my family </item>
              <item ID="GPP_eol_priorities_1-3"> Dying at home </item>
            </list>
            <br />
            <content
              styleCode="Bold">Treatment Preferences</content>
            <br />
            <content ID="GPP_eol_3">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_3_C"> If I am having significant pain or suffering, </content>
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_3_Q">these are my thoughts about Supportive and Palliative Care. </content>
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_3_I" styleCode="Answer"> I would like my doctors to consult a Supportive
            and Palliative Care Team to help treat my physical, emotional and spiritual discomfort,
            and to support my family. </content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content>In
            addition to the general advance care goals provided above, below are specific treatment
            preferences with respect to certain specific circumstances or situations.</content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_4">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_4_C">If my health ever deteriorates due to a terminal illness,
            and my doctors believe I will not be able to interact meaningfully with my family,
            friends, or surroundings, </content>
                <content ID="GPP_eol_4_Q">these are my thoughts
            about life-sustaining treatments.</content>
                <content ID="GPP_eol_4_I" styleCode="Answer">
            I would like for them to keep trying life-sustaining treatments until my healthcare
            agent decides it is time to stop and such treatments and let me die gently. </content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_6">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_6_C"> If I have a severe, irreversible brain injury or illness
            and can’t dress, feed, or bathe myself, or communicate my medical wishes, but doctors
            can keep me alive in this condition for a long period of time, </content>
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_6_Q">these are my thoughts about life-sustaining treatments.</content>
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_6_I" styleCode="Answer"> I would like for them to keep trying
            life-sustaining treatments until my healthcare agent decides it is time to stop and such
            treatments and let me die gently. </content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_8">Although I understand that, depending on the situation and
            circumstances, medical personnel may not be able to follow my wishes, here are <content
                ID="GPP_eol_8_Q">my general thoughts on cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR): </content>
                <br />
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_8_I" styleCode="Answer"> I want my healthcare agent to decide for me. </content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_10">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_10_Q">Where to spend final days:</content>
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_10_A" styleCode="Answer"> At home.</content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_eol_11">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_11_Q">Thought on hospice care:</content>
                <content
                ID="GPP_eol_11_A" styleCode="Answer">I would like to receive hospice care at home if
            possible. </content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content ID="GPP_eol_12">
              <content ID="GPP_eol_12_I">I understand that, in certain jurisdictions, if I have been
            diagnosed as pregnant and that diagnosis is known to my attending physician, medical
            treatment providers may refuse to follow my directives and provide life-sustaining
            treatment including artificially administered nutrition and hydration, as well as CPR
            and other resuscitation measures.</content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
          </text>
        </section>
      </component>

      <component>
        <section>
          <templateId root="2.16.840.1.113883.4.823.1.3.5" extension="2022-03-25" />
          <code code="81337-8" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC"
            displayName="Patient Goals, preferences, and priorities upon death" />
          <title mediaType="text/plain" representation="TXT" language="en-US">Preferences Upon Death</title>
          <text>
            <content ID="GPP_ud_1">
              <content ID="GPP_ud_1_Q" styleCode="Bold">Organ Donation:</content>
              <br />
              <content
                ID="GPP_ud_1_A" styleCode="Answer"> I would like to donate all organs and tissues
            that would be useful for someone else.</content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_ud_3">
              <content ID="GPP_ud_3_Q" styleCode="Bold">Autopsy:</content>
              <br />
              <content
                ID="GPP_ud_3_I" styleCode="Answer">I want an autopsy</content>
              <content
                ID="GPP_ud_3_C_1" styleCode="Answer">only if there are questions about my death or</content>
              <content
                ID="GPP_ud_3_C_2" styleCode="Answer">a law enforcement official requests it.</content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
            <content
              ID="GPP_ud_5">
              <content ID="GPP_ud_5_Q" styleCode="Bold">Death arrangements:</content>
              <br />
              <content
                ID="GPP_ud_5_A" styleCode="Answer"> Please call Jim Houston, my lawyer, for
            arrangements I have already made. I have purchased a funeral plat at Graceful Acres in
            Belmont NC and have life insurance policies filed with my lawyer that you should access
            if anything happens to me. </content>
            </content>
            <br />
            <br />
          </text>
        </section>
      </component>

